TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE: SELECT V_CLM_CDD.MBR_CDD_DAT , V_CLM_CDD.GRP_CDD_DAT , V_CLNT_CDD_LKP.RPT_PRCS_NB , V_CLNT_CDD_LKP.CLM_GID , V_PHMCY_CLM.MEDD_CVR_DRUG_IND , V_PHMCY_CLM.MEDB_IND FROM DWV_EDW.V_CLM_CDD , DWV_RBTS.V_CLNT_CDD_LKP , DWV_EDW.V_PHMCY_CLM WHERE DWV_RBTS.V_CLNT_CDD_LKP.EXTL_CLAIM_ID = DWV_EDW.V_PHMCY_CLM.CLM_NBR AND DWV_RBTS.V_CLNT_CDD_LKP.EXTL_CLAIM_SEQ = DWV_EDW.V_PHMCY_CLM.CLM_SEQ_NBR AND DWV_RBTS.V_CLNT_CDD_LKP.SRC_CD = DWV_EDW.V_PHMCY_CLM.ADJD_SRC_CD AND DWV_EDW.V_PHMCY_CLM.CLM_EVNT_GID = DWV_EDW.V_CLM_CDD.CLM_EVNT_GID AND DWV_EDW.V_PHMCY_CLM.MBR_ACCT_GID = DWV_EDW.V_CLM_CDD.MBR_ACCT_GID AND DWV_EDW.V_PHMCY_CLM.FILL_DT = DWV_EDW.V_CLM_CDD.FILL_DT AND DWV_RBTS.V_CLNT_CDD_LKP.RPT_PRCS_NB = $$RPT_PRCS_NB

The CLM_LVL1 from TCLAIM_RPT_DETL is sourced from the TAPC_DETAIL table, which LPADs 0's on the value. EDM does not have leading zeros, so have to trim them for the lookup value.

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: If the TRAN_TYP_CD = N then the claims are newly invoiced and this port should sum up the 2nd set of amount fields. If the TRAN_TYP_CD != N then the claims are adjustments and this port should sum up the 1st set of amount fields.
TRANSFORMFIELD.EXPRESSION:
decode(rtrim(in_TRAN_TYP_CD), 'N', TO_DECIMAL(in_RBATE_ACCESS + in_RBATE_MRKT_SHR + in_RBATE_ADMIN_FEE,5),
TO_DECIMAL(in_ACCS_RBAT_AMT + in_MKSR_RBAT_AMT + in_ADMN_FEE_AMT,5) )

WORKFLOWVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: This is the final filename value that is built during the worklet execution. It does not contain a file extension, and is used inside the worklet and passed to the workflow at the end of the execution.
WORKFLOWVARIABLE.NAME: $$FILENAME_FINAL_WKLT

WORKFLOWVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: This is the Statementing end date and is assigned by the workflow, to the worklet variable to be used in the mapping that builds the working flie.
WORKFLOWVARIABLE.NAME: $$STMT_END_DT_WKLT

WORKFLOWVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: This is the Payments reporting client name and is assigned by the workflow to the worklet variable. The value is used in target and source filenames built during the process.
WORKFLOWVARIABLE.NAME: $$RPT_CLNT_SHORT_NME_WKLT

WORKFLOWVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: This is the Payments reporting process number and is assigned by the workflow to the worklet variable. The value is used in some of the mappings that build the files throughout the process, and at the end of a successful execution it is used in a POST-SQL delete that is executed on the EDM system.
WORKFLOWVARIABLE.NAME: $$RPT_PRCS_NB_WKLT

WORKFLOWVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: This is the trigger file value and is assigned by the workflow prior to the worklet executon. It is used at the end of the worklet to remove the appropriate trigger file upon successful execution.
WORKFLOWVARIABLE.NAME: $$BLD_TRG_FLE_NME_WKLT

WORKFLOWVARIABLE.DESCRIPTION: This is the Detail filename value that is built during the worklet execution. It DOES contain a file extension, and is used inside the worklet but IS NOT passed to the workflow at the end of the execution.
WORKFLOWVARIABLE.NAME: $$FILENAME_DETAIL_WKLT

TASK.DESCRIPTION: This email task will send an email using the CLNT_EMAIL_WF variable assigned at the beginning of this workflow, informing all on the list that the process was successful.
TASK.NAME: Email_Client_Process_Successful

ATTRIBUTE.NAME: Email Subject
ATTRIBUTE.VALUE: Aetna Coventry quarterly invoice file was sent successfully

ATTRIBUTE.NAME: Email Text
ATTRIBUTE.VALUE:
The Coventry invoice file layout was built and the following file was sent to the CVS webtransport system.
$$FINAL_FILENAME_WF.gz

SESSION.DESCRIPTION: set rpt_prcs_stat_cd = F2 to indicate that there was a failure in either the build transformation or the SFTPs.
SESSION.NAME: s_m_Dummy_Parameter_Variable_Set_Status_Fail

ATTRIBUTE.NAME: Pre SQL
ATTRIBUTE.VALUE: update $$MVS_DB2_OWNER_WF.KSZ6020_RPT_PRCS_CNTL set rpt_prcs_stat_cd = 'F2' ,updt_ts = current timestamp ,updt_user_id = 'INFA' where rpt_prcs_nb = $$RPT_PRCS_NB_WF

ATTRIBUTE.NAME: Email Text
ATTRIBUTE.VALUE:
An error occured in the workflow %w running in %d.
Please check the workflow log to determine which session failed.
If this RPT_PRCS_NB is to be rerun, after fixing the error this workflow can only be rerun after the MVS $$MVS_DB2_OWNER.KSZ6020_RPT_PRCS_CNTL.RPT_PRCS_STAT_CD is set to 'R1' WHERE RPT_PRCS_NB = $$PRCS_NB_WF.
If the issue is not going to be fixed and this specific RPT_PRCS_NB will not be rerun for this workflow, then the RPT_PRCS_STAT_CD -=MUST=- be set to 'F'. Otherwise no other RPT_PRCS_NB will ever be run for this client until the current RPT_PRCS_STAT_CD of 'F2' is changed.

ATTRIBUTE.NAME: Email Text
ATTRIBUTE.VALUE:
The mapping %m ran in the %s session in the %w workflow ran in %d.
%t
%l
%r
Session Log is attached %g
Please check the workflow log to determine which session failed.
If this RPT_PRCS_NB is to be rerun, after fixing the error this workflow can only be rerun after the MVS $$MVS_DB2_OWNER.KSZ6020_RPT_PRCS_CNTL.RPT_PRCS_STAT_CD is set to 'R1' WHERE RPT_PRCS_NB = $$PRCS_NB_WF.
If the issue is not going to be fixed and this specific RPT_PRCS_NB will not be rerun for this workflow, then the RPT_PRCS_STAT_CD -=MUST=- be set to 'F'. Otherwise no other RPT_PRCS_NB will ever be run for this client until the current RPT_PRCS_STAT_CD of 'F2' is changed.
